Wow, Bp's gotten a lotta heat like real quick! Is it just your name, or your looks!?   LOL<br>
<br>
@thez GMT-6, or CST  Second question, not sure what you mean.

@thezmon221 Are those questions for me exclusively? cuz I didn't get the last one.<br>
<br>
@jon-h61 (I'm gonne refer to you as Jon, is that ok?) You know the cover for the new Coldplay album? It's like my avatar, except with BP in stead of MX, which stand for Mylo Xyloto, which stands for absolutely nothing. I know it's idiotic, but before it came out and I found out it sucks, I went to their website where they let (do they still do?) you "build your own Mylo Xyloto art", and I chose BP which stand for the initials of my nickname here in University praxis.

"A certain degree of knowledge" Doesn't mean he can't be a newbie, but I can sort of see where you are coming from. Anything to say on other people?<br>
<br>
@BP: 2 isn't really considered a bandwagon. I guess 3 would be a BW if it had some momentum as well.

@zmon: What do you remember about kondi?<br>
<br>
@kondi:  What do you remember about zmon?

I'm sorry if you're telling the truth but... I don't really believe your claim.<br>
<br>
@kondi: Was myko actually scum in that game or are you just assuming he was from the way he acted?

kondi: That doesn't solve much. The mafia will easily target someone else.<br>
<br>
@joker: I was never asked for reasons for my reads, so the only one I displayed was where prompted: MonkeyMan. Apart from that, I haven't effectively posted ISOs. Can you please explain to me why I'm scum? Because your reason just doesn't really make sense. I asked the question in the beginning, and ICE called me out. Why would he bus me so early in the game? There is so much risk involved that it's not a rational decision to make.

@everyone<br>
<br>
going to be gone from the forum till about 5-6pm u.s. Eastern time tomorrow. Spring break has ended and I have to fly back to college.

Nope, I have no problem with it, jon. I know that you would have committed before. Just out of curiosity: How interested are you in keeping your image as of right now to where you would not hammer one of your scummiest reads because some people will think you're scum?<br>
<br>
@Monkey: To be honest, with the way you are acting, you're becoming more of a distraction and even if you aren't mafia, it kind of benefits the town. We've gotten rid of the scummiest player on D1 and if you're acting so scummy that when some people (even me to an extent) may believe that you are telling the truth in your claim, but still see you as scummy, the lynch still helps the town because, like I said, it gets rid of a distraction. In any case, we will definitely have some things to consider, no matter what you flip. I'm bound to take a lot of heat since I was probably the biggest benefactor, but joker may also take heat for his safeguarding of you. We won't know until it's over.

@DCL I misspoke on my I'm sold declaration. That was meant for ICE and thez, which I am still sold on. You? I did think your push for a monkey lynch despite the PR claim was scummy. But then I realized that not everyone had the same read on monkey that I did, which was unfortunate.<br>
<br>
I react to the game as it comes to me, and my opinions shift accordingly. I do think there is a good possibility that you are scum, but not as convinced as I am that thez is. Hence, I am focusing and voting for him.

@ thez I'm not in the business of convincing scum that they are scum. My read on you and ICE still stands, for reasons I've already expressed. And if you and DCI are going to try and undermine my credibility because I read the bandwagon on monkey as scum driven, so be it. I wasn't 100 percent sure that monkey was town, more like 90 percent, which was more than enough for me to defend him. I'm seriously concerned with the prevailing attitude that "well the monkey lynch was justified cause he was acting scummy." Thats bad town at best, scum trying to cover up a PR lynch at worst.  I find it interesting y'all are trying to undermine me for a correct read.<br>
<br>
@DCI he wasn't acting scummy. He was targeted by thez early and thez railroaded monkey all day one. Nothing monkey could have said would have stopped the scum driven bandwagon against him, they were pretty confident he was a PR. The name of the game of their strategy to get him lynched being "where there is smoke there is fire" which town bit hook line and sinker.  He didn't soft role claim, he telegraphed he would claim if he hit l-1, which he did. Stop focusing on single posts and put the story together, unless you at scum. In which case continue to not do this. As far as him not being polite, that read can be applied to thez and ICE, who are both pretty rude as well. Do you consider them scum for that? And monkey knew he was going to die, so I didn't read too much into his "screw this " mentality late game.

@DCL I never tried to get town cred for defending monkey. Rather, I wanted town to realize how monkeys bandwagon was manufactured. I was accused of being "too sure of monkeys town affiliation" so I was forced to explain why I thought he was town. After that happened I was accused of trying to get towncred, another manufactured scum accusation against me.<br>
<br>
The entire case against me is pretty weak, just a lot of smoke to trick town into another mislynch.

@Elmo<br>
<br>
Changing your mind isn't inherently scummy, but what your doing seems both inconsistent and incoherent. It doesn't make a whole lot of sense from a town perspective.

@Antihero<br>
<br>
The reason we are find with a lynch before the deadline is because we have hit a really slow part of the game. We have are ideas of who is scum, and we need to see a flip or two to see if we are on the right track and to get the game moving again.

Wow this game has taken a weird turn. I don't even know what to make of hoko.  Or the bandwagon on him.<br>
<br>
@hoko I know you are having computer issues but you really need to set aside some time to compile your thoughts.

If jon's scum, he's playing very aggressively. Casting the hammer vote two Days in a row on people that scum!jon would know were going to flip Town? I still don't buy it, but with my track record I clearly don't know my ass from a teakettle in this game. Hell, I was even starting to suspect ICEninja because of his active role in both mislynches. (Yes, I am aware of my own active role in both mislynches as well.) <br>
<br>
@Antihero: We haven't lynched thezmon221 yet and he hasn't flipped. If we want to hunt scum in the wagons, we should look at the people in the wagons that led to lynches.

@antihero, Just to be clear, you seem to think it is likely that thez could be scum. But you are going to sheep IAAUN and leave your vote one of the two people accusing thez right now? No offense, but this seems like an odd position to hold. <br>
<br>
@IAAUN, nice to see you around, I think I asked you a question a page back that I would still appreciate seeing you answer.

@antihero, thanks for clearing that up, the "/slapself" part made me wonder if there was some sarcasm involved.<br>
<br>
Also, I think you can see why I wanted you to clarify your case against me, I had completely forgotten about the wagon analysis stuff. Looking back at that info it seems like there is some useful information there.

@MathGirl: Unless you know something I don't, we're at MyLo.<br>
<br>
@Haze: Mass-Claim at this point may work, but it may not. My impression is we still have at least one more Vanilla Townie, if not more.
